==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Precognosce
<hw>Pre*cog"nosce</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>praecognoscere</ets> to foreknow.]</ety> <fld>(Scots Law)</fld>
<def>To examine beforehand, as witnesses or evidence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A committee of nine <qex>precognoscing</qex> the chances.</q>
<rj><qau>Masson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Precollection</ent>⟦br⟧
